Oh. shut the fuck up!

255
00:13:30.352 --> 00:13:31.477
Yeah?

256
00:13:31.478 --> 00:13:32.521
Open up.

257
00:13:43.365 --> 00:13:45.491
You do not need
to be checking on me

258
00:13:45.492 --> 00:13:46.409
if that's what you were doing.

259
00:13:47.911 --> 00:13:49.245
Thought I'd say hello. is all.

260
00:13:49.246 --> 00:13:50.913
May I?

261
00:13:50.914 --> 00:13:52.915
How'd you know where I live?

262
00:13:52.916 --> 00:13:56.086
I found out a whole bunch
of things about your new life.

263
00:13:57.546 --> 00:13:59.005
'Cause you're
a detective now. are ya?

264
00:14:05.095 --> 00:14:08.097
You know. when I was in prison.

265
00:14:08.098 --> 00:14:10.475
every day and night.
I thought about you.

266
00:14:11.268 --> 00:14:12.936
It was the only thing
that kept my sanity.

267
00:14:14.229 --> 00:14:15.564
The thought of seeing you again.

268
00:14:16.940 --> 00:14:18.983
I'm glad you're free.

269
00:14:18.984 --> 00:14:20.360
but things are different.

270
00:14:22.612 --> 00:14:24.363
Aye.

271
00:14:24.364 --> 00:14:26.032
'Cause of your boyfriend?

272
00:14:27.450 --> 00:14:30.452
I hear he's quite
an interesting wee man.

273
00:14:30.453 --> 00:14:32.621
A bit of a thief.
break a couple of legs.

274
00:14:32.622 --> 00:14:34.291
'Cause you and I have
never hurt a fly.

275
00:14:36.334 --> 00:14:38.294
He does what he has to.
to survive.

276
00:14:38.295 --> 00:14:39.628
He has not had it easy.

277
00:14:39.629 --> 00:14:42.506
but he's brilliant and kind

278
00:14:42.507 --> 00:14:44.174
and he gets me.

279
00:14:44.175 --> 00:14:45.427
Compared to me?

280
00:14:47.971 --> 00:14:51.140
I've known you and your
whole family my whole life.

281
00:14:51.141 --> 00:14:52.517
I don't have one anymore.

282
00:14:54.394 --> 00:14:56.021
And neither does he.

283
00:14:57.564 --> 00:14:59.316
He understands the pain of that.

284
00:15:00.191 --> 00:15:02.444
Does he believe
in something beyond himself?

285
00:15:03.737 --> 00:15:05.447
- Yeah. he does.
- What?

286
00:15:07.490 --> 00:15:08.992
Me.

287
00:15:10.660 --> 00:15:12.536
Brendan.

288
00:15:12.537 --> 00:15:15.247
I do respect you.

289
00:15:15.248 --> 00:15:18.668
But I agreed to hold the crate
for Ireland. not for you.

290
00:15:24.591 --> 00:15:26.134
Please. can you leave?

291
00:15:35.352 --> 00:15:37.187
Glad he's takin' care
of you. Bridget.

292
00:15:49.324 --> 00:15:51.700
Alright. Sean.
keep your eyes on the street.

293
00:15:51.701 --> 00:15:53.035
Keep the car runnin'.

294
00:15:53.036 --> 00:15:54.370
What I need you to do

295
00:15:54.371 --> 00:15:56.163
is to scare
the shit out of everyone

296
00:15:56.164 --> 00:15:57.623
and make sure they're
face down on the floor.

297
00:15:57.624 --> 00:15:59.124
I don't want
anyone looking up at me

298
00:15:59.125 --> 00:16:00.376
while I'm doing
my thing with the hand.

299
00:16:00.377 --> 00:16:02.795
Yeah. okay. I got it. Jimmy.

300
00:16:02.796 --> 00:16:04.463
Yeah. I bet
they got a safe in there.

301
00:16:04.464 --> 00:16:06.090
- You wanna crack that too?
- No. I'm just gonna

302
00:16:06.091 --> 00:16:07.716
grab some jewelry
and get the fuck out.

303
00:16:07.717 --> 00:16:09.551
Are you sure? I mean.
that's where they're gonna

304
00:16:09.552 --> 00:16:11.178
- keep all the good shit.
- Hey. shit-for-brains.

305
00:16:11.179 --> 00:16:12.721
am I gonna have
a problem with you?

306
00:16:12.722 --> 00:16:14.264
No. no. I'm good.
Let's fuckin' do this.

307
00:16:14.265 --> 00:16:16.725
Good. All right.
Everyone ready?

308
00:16:16.726 --> 00:16:18.143
Yup.

309
00:16:18.144 --> 00:16:20.562
And don't shoot no one.
All right?

310
00:16:20.563 --> 00:16:22.773
Fuckin' hand is
starting to stink!

311
00:16:22.774 --> 00:16:25.359
Let's go!

312
00:16:33.243 --> 00:16:35.077
Everybody get on the floor!

313
00:16:35.078 --> 00:16:36.578
You're getting fuckin' robbed!
Face the fuckin' wall!

314
00:16:36.579 --> 00:16:38.539
Don't you even think of
touching that panic button!

315
00:16:38.540 --> 00:16:40.207
Get your fuckin' face
on the floor!

316
00:16:40.208 --> 00:16:42.418
Head down!
Eyes on the fuckin' floor!

317
00:16:42.419 --> 00:16:44.253
I see those fuckin' eyes.

318
00:16:44.254 --> 00:16:45.463
I swear to God
I'll blow your head off!

319
00:16:46.756 --> 00:16:48.633
Keep those fuckin' eyes down!

320
00:16:51.761 --> 00:16:54.263
I don't want to see
any fuckin' eyes back there!

321
00:16:54.264 --> 00:16:57.099
Eyes down! Head down!

322
00:16:57.100 --> 00:16:59.184
Eyes down on the fuckin' floor!

323
00:16:59.185 --> 00:17:01.312
I don't want to see
any fuckin' eyes!

324
00:17:03.189 --> 00:17:04.649
All right. boys. let's go!

325
00:17:25.170 --> 00:17:26.795
Can I get you another one?

326
00:17:26.796 --> 00:17:28.047
If you insist.

327
00:17:29.799 --> 00:17:31.675
Kind of empty
in here today. huh?

328
00:17:31.676 --> 00:17:33.343
Yeah. it's the Javits Center.

329
00:17:33.344 --> 00:17:35.137
the whole
neighborhood's employed.

330
00:17:35.138 --> 00:17:37.639
I was making more money
when people were broke.

331
00:17:38.892 --> 00:17:41.226
Yeah. huh?

332
00:17:41.227 --> 00:17:44.188
Oh. Sweeney must be
licking his lips.

333
00:17:44.189 --> 00:17:45.689
all the security. construction.

334
00:17:45.690 --> 00:17:47.232
and labor going on.

335
00:17:47.233 --> 00:17:48.817
Ah. you know how it is. Glenn.

336
00:17:48.818 --> 00:17:51.654
Yeah. What about
the Italians. I wonder?

337
00:17:53.156 --> 00:17:55.783
Dagos must be
getting a piece. no?

338
00:17:55.784 --> 00:17:58.285
Dagos are dagos.
It's the way of the world.

339
00:17:58.286 --> 00:17:59.870
Oh. you're right.

340
00:17:59.871 --> 00:18:01.663
What I don't understand.

341
00:18:01.664 --> 00:18:03.290
I mean.

342
00:18:03.291 --> 00:18:05.209
Gambinos must be losin'
their fuckin' minds

343
00:18:05.210 --> 00:18:06.752
the biggest construction project

344
00:18:06.753 --> 00:18:08.170
in the history of New York

345
00:18:08.171 --> 00:18:09.588
falls into the lap of the Irish.

346
00:18:09.589 --> 00:18:10.507
Yeah. go figure.

347
00:18:11.800 --> 00:18:14.176
Yeah. well. maybe there is a God

348
00:18:14.177 --> 00:18:15.677
and maybe he's Irish.

349
00:18:15.678 --> 00:18:17.222
No doubt.

350
00:18:20.850 --> 00:18:23.186
So. you seen any dagos
comin' in here lately?

351
00:18:24.354 --> 00:18:26.522
What're you talking about?

352
00:18:26.523 --> 00:18:30.234
Well. I'm just curious who
Sweeney's been dealing with.

353
00:18:30.235 --> 00:18:32.319
Is it that fat fuck
Frank Mancuso?

354
00:18:32.320 --> 00:18:34.404
Or that other grease ball
everybody's talkin' about...

355
00:18:34.405 --> 00:18:35.657
John Gotti?

356
00:18:37.826 --> 00:18:39.244
Now how would I know
a thing like that?

357
00:18:40.703 --> 00:18:42.371
It's conversation. Ray.

358
00:18:42.372 --> 00:18:44.873
I'm just. uh. musing.

359
00:18:44.874 --> 00:18:45.874
Is that a word for you?

360
00:18:45.875 --> 00:18:47.751
Yeah. well.

361
00:18:47.752 --> 00:18:49.837
keep those kind of questions
to yourself. Glenn.

362
00:18:49.838 --> 00:18:51.797
if you know what's good for ya.

363
00:18:51.798 --> 00:18:54.634
Calm down Ray.
I'm musing.

364
00:18:55.885 --> 00:18:57.428
Sweeney wants to see you.

365
00:18:59.430 --> 00:19:01.682
How'd Sweeney know I was here?

366
00:19:01.683 --> 00:19:03.225
It's three in the afternoon.

367
00:19:03.226 --> 00:19:04.561
You're a fuckin' drunk.
Where else would you be?

368
00:19:09.482 --> 00:19:10.941
Huh.

369
00:19:10.942 --> 00:19:13.236
Ain't easy being
a parent. is it. Ray?

370
00:19:21.578 --> 00:19:22.995
This it?
This is all you took?

371
00:19:22.996 --> 00:19:24.371
That's it.

372
00:19:24.372 --> 00:19:26.248
We left the fingerprints
and got out.

373
00:19:26.249 --> 00:19:27.666
They had a safe
in the back. too.

374
00:19:27.667 --> 00:19:30.419
- but we didn't touch it.
- Did anybody see you?

375
00:19:30.420 --> 00:19:32.713
Did you fuck this up in any way?

376
00:19:32.714 --> 00:19:34.673
No. No one saw a thing.

377
00:19:34.674 --> 00:19:36.300
No. Mickey here scared
the shit out of 'em.

378
00:19:36.301 --> 00:19:38.510
Didn't you?
It was an easy score.

379
00:19:38.511 --> 00:19:40.304
You know. Boss. we could
probably go back some time.

380
00:19:40.305 --> 00:19:41.805
crack that safe if you like.

381
00:19:41.806 --> 00:19:43.432
The fuck you will.

382
00:19:43.433 --> 00:19:45.392
What about this? You want us
to fence it for ya?

383
00:19:45.393 --> 00:19:47.269
No. no. we're not
gonna fence anything.

384
00:19:47.270 --> 00:19:48.770
This is gonna stay
right here with me

385
00:19:48.771 --> 00:19:51.274
till this whole thing
fuckin' blows over.

386
00:19:52.066 --> 00:19:54.527
All right. what's your next
move there. Bobby Fischer?

387
00:19:55.987 --> 00:19:58.030
I figure we take
Zaccaro out of town.

388
00:19:58.031 --> 00:20:00.282
Where to?

389
00:20:00.283 --> 00:20:01.742
Near Boston.

390
00:20:01.743 --> 00:20:03.619
You know. make it seem
like he's fleeing to Canada.

391
00:20:03.620 --> 00:20:05.495
There's plenty of places
up there to hit.

392
00:20:05.496 --> 00:20:07.039
We'll leave first thing
in the morning.

393
00:20:07.040 --> 00:20:08.665
Yeah. you know what?

394
00:20:08.666 --> 00:20:11.627
I got a friend up there
runs a place. Corktown Pub.

395
00:20:11.628 --> 00:20:13.378
Liam O'Shaughnessy's place.

396
00:20:13.379 --> 00:20:14.796
he's a Southie.

397
00:20:14.797 --> 00:20:17.299
Go up there. rob his place.
He'll help you.

398
00:20:17.300 --> 00:20:19.801
You mean rob his own bar?

399
00:20:19.802 --> 00:20:21.970
Fuckin' beat up his own mother
if I told him to.

400
00:20:23.514 --> 00:20:25.350
- Go. on your way.
- Yes. sir.

401
00:20:30.063 --> 00:20:31.647
What do you think
their chances are

402
00:20:31.648 --> 00:20:33.899
- of pulling this off?
- These two?

403
00:20:33.900 --> 00:20:35.651
About as good as a fart
in a fuckin' windstorm.

404
00:20:37.695 --> 00:20:38.987
Fart in a windstorm.
That's good.

405
00:20:38.988 --> 00:20:41.031
That's good.

406
00:20:50.875 --> 00:20:52.584
Hey. Lina. how you doin'?

407
00:20:52.585 --> 00:20:53.836
Get the fuck outta my way!

408
00:20:55.838 --> 00:20:57.381
No. no matter how fuckin' late.

409
00:20:57.382 --> 00:20:58.507
even four or five
in the morning.

410
00:20:58.508 --> 00:21:00.467
he always comes home!

411
00:21:00.468 --> 00:21:02.594
Lina. I'm sure that
there's an explanation.

412
00:21:02.595 --> 00:21:04.721
No. John. he missed
our daughter's christening

413
00:21:04.722 --> 00:21:06.848
this morning! Nothing would
keep him from that!

414
00:21:06.849 --> 00:21:08.600
Here. Here.
Have one of these.

415
00:21:08.601 --> 00:21:10.018
I just had this machine
imported from Italy.

416
00:21:10.019 --> 00:21:11.812
I don't care! I don't want
no fucking coffee!

417
00:21:11.813 --> 00:21:12.980
I'm nervous enough as it is!

418
00:21:12.981 --> 00:21:14.523
All right. listen.
Lina. come on.

419
00:21:14.524 --> 00:21:15.857
I ain't seen him
in a couple of days.

420
00:21:15.858 --> 00:21:16.901
But I'm sure
that he's gonna turn up.

421
00:21:19.529 --> 00:21:21.029
Is he with his goomah?

422
00:21:21.030 --> 00:21:23.115
Ah. come on. Goomah? What are
you talkin' about goomah?

423
00:21:23.116 --> 00:21:24.700
Oh. shut the fuck up.

424
00:21:24.701 --> 00:21:26.493
I know. all right?

425
00:21:26.494 --> 00:21:29.496
I overheard him
talking to her on the phone.

426
00:21:29.497 --> 00:21:32.040
Well. that is news to me.

427
00:21:32.041 --> 00:21:34.710
Some Irish bitch he met
on the West Side named Erin.

428
00:21:34.711 --> 00:21:36.628
And I swear to God.
if he's with her.

429
00:21:36.629 --> 00:21:38.506
I will scratch
her fuckin' eyes out!

430
00:21:40.425 --> 00:21:42.968
Lina. go home. Okay?

431
00:21:42.969 --> 00:21:45.555
I'm gonna go look for him
myself. personally. all right?

432
00:21:48.516 --> 00:21:50.100
I got a brutta sensazione.

433
00:21:50.101 --> 00:21:52.561
No. come on.
Don't say that.

434
00:21:52.562 --> 00:21:54.771
Come on. Don't talk like that.
Come on. Come here.

435
00:21:54.772 --> 00:21:57.650
I got no proof. but I can't
shake this feeling.

436
00:21:59.402 --> 00:22:00.862
I think he's dead.

437
00:22:12.623 --> 00:22:14.709
- Where's your crazy half?
- Jeez!

438
00:22:16.919 --> 00:22:18.921
At the 596 getting soused.

439
00:22:20.757 --> 00:22:24.885
What are you doin'
sitting in the dark? Huh?

440
00:22:24.886 --> 00:22:27.929
There is something
I didn't tell you. Jimmy.

441
00:22:27.930 --> 00:22:30.891
Brendan Cahill
asked me for a favor.

442
00:22:32.894 --> 00:22:34.144
What kind of favor?

443
00:22:37.440 --> 00:22:41.611
He asked me
to hold something for him.

444
00:22:42.779 --> 00:22:45.113
A package.

445
00:22:45.114 --> 00:22:46.032
A weapon.

446
00:22:47.867 --> 00:22:49.035
And you said no. right?

447
00:22:50.620 --> 00:22:52.746
Jimmy. I want to do it.

448
00:22:52.747 --> 00:22:54.874
For the cause.
Not for him.

449
00:22:56.542 --> 00:22:58.085
I said I'd keep it at the dock

450
00:22:58.086 --> 00:22:59.753
until he could ship it
to Ireland and that's it.

451
00:22:59.754 --> 00:23:01.047
I am the only one
who can do this.

452
00:23:02.799 --> 00:23:03.966
That was fucking stupid.

453
00:23:06.469 --> 00:23:08.053
Excuse me?

454
00:23:08.054 --> 00:23:09.805
You had to be smuggled
out of Ireland

455
00:23:09.806 --> 00:23:12.224
to avoid being shot
on sight by the Brits.

456
00:23:12.225 --> 00:23:14.976
You got out. Bridget.
You got a new life.

457
00:23:14.977 --> 00:23:16.645
Why would you
wanna fuck that up?

458
00:23:16.646 --> 00:23:19.022
It's a new life.
but I still want

459
00:23:19.023 --> 00:23:20.690
to make a difference
whatever way I can.

460
00:23:20.691 --> 00:23:23.652
If that means holding
one package for a few days.

461
00:23:23.653 --> 00:23:25.112
- that's more than worth it.
- No. no. no. No.

462
00:23:25.113 --> 00:23:26.947
I know how this works.
All right?

463
00:23:26.948 --> 00:23:29.658
One turns into two. then he's
asking for something else.

464
00:23:29.659 --> 00:23:32.077
- Don't fuckin' kid yourself.
- I'm not kidding...

465
00:23:32.078 --> 00:23:34.622
I'm not kidding myself.

466
00:23:39.168 --> 00:23:40.545
It's a few days...

467
00:23:42.088 --> 00:23:43.672
then I'm done with it.

468
00:23:43.673 --> 00:23:44.882
Done with him.

469
00:23:48.553 --> 00:23:50.012
Well. make sure
he understands that.

470
00:24:05.611 --> 00:24:07.612
Hit us again. Ray!

471
00:24:25.798 --> 00:24:26.882
How're we doing. Erin?

472
00:24:29.802 --> 00:24:32.304
"We." as in the royal "we"?

473
00:24:33.848 --> 00:24:35.516
Here. let me buy you a drink.

474
00:24:37.977 --> 00:24:39.604
Or you want to buy me one?

475
00:24:41.189 --> 00:24:42.106
Piss off.

476
00:24:43.733 --> 00:24:45.151
All right.

477
00:24:45.985 --> 00:24:48.153
I was just comin' to ask
how you were. that's all.

478
00:24:48.154 --> 00:24:49.654
Oh. that's all.

479
00:24:51.157 --> 00:24:53.116
How do you expect me to be?

480
00:24:53.117 --> 00:24:54.827
I don't know.

481
00:24:56.078 --> 00:24:57.997
I saw what you did.

482
00:25:00.917 --> 00:25:02.876
Excuse me?

483
00:25:02.877 --> 00:25:04.586
From my window.

484
00:25:04.587 --> 00:25:06.796
You and Vinnie Zaccaro.

485
00:25:08.674 --> 00:25:10.091
In the car.

486
00:25:13.054 --> 00:25:14.638
Don't worry.
I won't rat you out.

487
00:25:14.639 --> 00:25:16.641
I don't give
two shits about him.

488
00:25:17.600 --> 00:25:20.186
But I'm a lot poorer for it.
if you know what I mean.

489
00:25:21.771 --> 00:25:23.605
You're a nice girl. Erin.

490
00:25:23.606 --> 00:25:25.107
Something good will
come your way. I know it.

491
00:25:28.819 --> 00:25:31.029
Look at you.

492
00:25:31.030 --> 00:25:33.157
straight from the looney bin
and filled with good cheer.

493
00:25:35.618 --> 00:25:37.036
If you don't mind...

494
00:25:37.995 --> 00:25:40.957
I don't need sages tellin' me
my future when I can...

495
00:25:42.792 --> 00:25:44.292
when I can see it's pretty grim.

496
00:25:44.293 --> 00:25:45.920
so piss off. Mickey.

497
00:25:55.054 --> 00:25:58.223
Here. that's for you.

498
00:26:02.853 --> 00:26:04.896
I did a little job
for Mr. Sweeney.

499
00:26:04.897 --> 00:26:06.189
But I kept this piece.

500
00:26:06.190 --> 00:26:07.817
I want you to have it.

501
00:26:13.197 --> 00:26:16.116
I don't get it.
What do you want from me?

502
00:26:16.117 --> 00:26:19.411
No. no. I-I don't want nothin'.

503
00:26:19.412 --> 00:26:22.831
I just. but. uh...

504
00:26:22.832 --> 00:26:27.335
if you'd like to talk sometime.

505
00:26:27.336 --> 00:26:28.838
I'd like that.

506
00:26:31.257 --> 00:26:33.216
You know. I ain't got
many people I can talk to.

507
00:26:33.217 --> 00:26:34.635
you know.

508
00:26:36.220 --> 00:26:37.638
Okay.

509
00:26:41.767 --> 00:26:44.729
All right.
See you around.

510
